      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're probably looking for the right way to take inspiration from the urban landscape without actually being a caricature of it. I'd say the key to an authentic \"urban\" aesthetic is to focus on the grittier, more raw aspects of city life - think dark colors, industrial textures, and a general sense of neglect or decay. You can draw from the likes of old-school New York City graffiti, Chicago's South Side, or LA's lowrider culture, but be careful not to co-opt the style without giving proper credit or compensation to the communities that actually embody it.",
