      "content": "thanks for the tips. so when you mention those specific places like the south side of chicago or the lowrider culture, are you saying that certain styles are inherently tied to certain groups? like, if i'm designing for an \"urban\" vibe, should i be looking at specific racial or ethnic aesthetics to make it feel real? i just don't want to accidentally make it look like a generic \"city\" look that misses the actual soul of the culture.",
